# 🎓 Task-1: Digital Literacy Infographic

## 📌 Overview
This repository contains my submission for Task-1 as the Student Digital Ambassador.  
I created a one-page infographic to help my batchmates understand **Digital Literacy** and why it matters.

## 🖼️ Infographic
The infographic covers:
- ✅ What digital literacy is  
- ✅ Useful digital tools for students  
- ✅ Safe internet practices  

## 📝 Project Report
I used Canva to design the infographic because of its simple drag‑and‑drop interface and free templates.  
The design explains digital literacy, highlights tools like Google Drive and Grammarly, and emphasizes safe internet practices such as strong passwords and avoiding suspicious links.  

One interesting part of the process was simplifying complex ideas into short, impactful visuals.  
The challenge was balancing text and graphics so the slide looked clear but not overcrowded.  
Overall, the infographic shows that digital literacy is about both technical skills and responsible online behavior.

